CSS Full Tutorial: 
	- CSS Unit

CSS Units come in a few diffeent flavors

1. Absolute Units:
	- Pixels(px):
	 pt, cm, cmm, in etc.
2. Percentage - are mainly used for widths, and pretty easy to understand.
- Relative their parent(except on height, where things get weird)


1. There are two typed of relative units:
	- Relative to font size 
	Relative to the viewport
Even though it shounds complicated, once you play around with them a little it is not too bad!.

CSS Units - Relative to font size:
	em and rem(and many other less commn ones)
	
Relative to the viewport
	- vew, vh, vmin, vmax


